Scrap Language Description

The scrap language is an object oriented, strictly 
typed language, and share many similarities with 
Java and C#. This document gives examples of what 
the language will be able to do IN IT'S FINAL STATE, 
and is by all means to be considered a work in 
progress.  


Hello World Example
	import System;
	class Main {
		public void main() {
			System.Print("Hello, World!\n");
		}
	}


Fibonacci Example
	import System;
	class Main {
		public void main() {
			int num = fib(5);
			System.Print("Fib(5): " + num);
		}

		private int fib(unsigned n) {
			if (n <= 1) return n;
			return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2);
		}
	}


Inheritance Example
	import System;
	class Main {
		public void main() {
			// Create a new Bar-object
			Bar b = new Bar();

			// Prints "N(): 6"
			System.Println("N(): " + b.N());
		}
	}

	class FooA { 
		protected int n = 6;
	}

	class Bar : FooA, FooB {
		public int N() {
			return n;
		}
	}
